        <body>       

                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>116 Cumberland St<lb/></p>
            <p>Brooklyn July 16th 1888<lb/>
                Rev Dr S. Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>Through the efforts<lb/> of our Minister Mr Friedlander<lb/> the Board of Trustees has called<lb/> a special congregational meeting<lb/> which is to be held next<lb/> Sunday&#44; the 22nd Inst in the<lb/> School room corner Boerum<lb/> Place &#38; State St to treat upon the question whether to abolish<lb/> the pews of our Cong&#44; which<lb/> has been established in our<lb/> Cong&#44; since the year 1880 or<lb/> remain as it is now.<lb/></p>
            <p>And knowing you as the illustrious<lb/> leader of all the orthodox Rabbis<lb/> in America&#44; and our Congregation<lb/> professing to be orthodox&#44; I&#44; with<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>the advice of our minister<lb/> &#38; the board of Trustees&#44; beg<lb/> to request your presence<lb/> at the said meeting.<lb/></p>
            <p>please let me know either<lb/> of your acceptance or of<lb/> your declination of the<lb/> invitation and oblige<lb/> yours Respectfully<lb/> Mr. Phillips Presnt<lb/> of Cong Baith Israel<lb/> Brooklyn<lb/> Per<lb/> J. K. Stenchever<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
